  "texts": [
    "Dataset A was derived from the MHI's comprehensive CAG videos database, which contains 182,418 videos of LCA or RCA in DICOM format, captured at 15 frames per second, and includes patients aged 18 years and older, spanning the period from January 1, 2017, to December 31, 2021.",
    "The dataset was used for the training, validation, and testing of DeepCoro.",
    "Clinical reports detail the percentage of coronary artery segment stenosis, ranging from 0 to 100%, associated to these videos as described by the interventional cardiologist after visual assessment.",
    "Segments with ≥70% stenosis were classified as severe, while those with less were labeled as nonsevere.",
    "After applying Algorithms 1-5 to this database, we obtained a final dataset of 44,139 videos from 8057 patients with associated stenosis percentages from clinical reports."
  ],
